REGULATIONS FROM THE E.P.A. OR

00:43.209 --> 00:44.210 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
OTHER PLACES THAT WOULD PROTECT

00:44.210 --> 00:45.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WATER OR AIR QUALITY?

00:45.845 --> 00:46.880 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I MEAN, DOES THE MILITARY HAVE

00:46.880 --> 00:48.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AN EXEMPTION FROM THOSE?

00:48.515 --> 00:49.449 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
>> YEAH, I MEAN, THERE ARE

00:49.449 --> 00:50.550 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
STRINGENT ENVIRONMENTAL

00:50.550 --> 00:52.252 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PROTECTION AGENCY REGULATIONS,

00:52.252 --> 00:53.820 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SOME OF WHICH APPLY TO THE

00:53.820 --> 00:55.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PENTAGON AND SOME WHICH DON'T.

00:55.255 --> 00:57.824 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
IN THE CASE OF OPEN BURNS, THE

00:57.824 --> 00:59.092 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PENTAGON'S ESSENTIALLY BURNING

00:59.092 --> 01:00.960 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WHAT'S DEFINED AS HAZARDOUS

01:00.960 --> 01:04.664 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WASTE.

01:04.664 --> 01:06.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AND THE E.P.A. REGULATED THE

01:06.833 --> 01:08.468 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BURNING OF HAZARDOUS WASTE BACK

01:08.468 --> 01:09.102 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
IN THE 1980s.

01:09.102 --> 01:09.803 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SO, 30 YEARS OR SO YEARS AGO.

01:09.803 --> 01:10.937 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
EXPLOSIVES WERE ADMITTEDLY

01:10.937 --> 01:11.971 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DIFFICULT TO DEAL WITH.

01:11.971 --> 01:13.673 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SO AT THE TIME THEY CREATED A

01:13.673 --> 01:14.707 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LITTLE BIT OF A LOOPHOLE THAT

01:14.707 --> 01:16.576 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SAID THAT THE PENTAGON AND OTHER

01:16.576 --> 01:18.244 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SPECIALIZED COMPANIES THAT DEAL

01:18.244 --> 01:19.979 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ONLY IN EXPLOSIVES CAN CONTINUE

01:19.979 --> 01:21.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TO BURN THAT STUFF IF THAT'S THE

01:21.381 --> 01:22.549 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ONLY WAY THEY CAN GET RID OF IT,

01:22.549 --> 01:23.950 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BUT ONLY UNTIL THEY IMPROVE

01:23.950 --> 01:25.218 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TECHNOLOGY, FIGURE OUT A BETTER

01:25.218 --> 01:26.686 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WAY TO DEAL WITH IT, AT WHICH

01:26.686 --> 01:28.721 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
POINT THEY WOULD BE REQUIRED BY

01:28.721 --> 01:29.956 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
THE REGULATIONS TO MOVE TO THOSE

01:29.956 --> 01:31.691 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ALTERNATIVES.

01:31.691 --> 01:32.959 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
THOSE NOW EXIST, THEY HAVE FOR A

01:32.959 --> 01:34.027 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LONG TIME, BUT THE DEPARTMENT OF

01:34.027 --> 01:35.495 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DEFENSE STILL LEANS VERY HEAVILY

01:35.495 --> 01:37.030 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ON BURNING AS THEIR STANDBY

01:37.030 --> 01:38.031 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PROCESS.

01:38.031 --> 01:39.099 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
>> Sreenivasan: HOW WIDESPREAD

01:39.099 --> 01:39.899 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
IS THIS AROUND THE COUNTRY?

01:39.899 --> 01:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I MEAN, YOU HAVE A MAP IN ONE

01:40.600 --> 01:41.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
OF YOUR STORIES.

01:41.067 --> 01:42.035 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HOW MANY DIFFERENT SITES ARE

01:42.035 --> 01:43.403 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
THERE THAT ARE DOING THIS THAT

01:43.403 --> 01:45.672 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
